               <head>: Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 4 works (a-d)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Collection of miscellaneous prose works on Sufism, several ascribed to Yaʿqūb Charkhī. Volume note dated, individual items dated (items c and d), Shavvāl 992/October 1584 or slightly later. Folios unbound, heavily stained. Some folio disordered and lost. Later stained leather binding, with tooled edge. Stamped foliation; original discontinuous Persian foliation in some items. Annotations and purchase notes of later owners. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1162-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="4r">ff. 1v-4r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. 
</p>
                        <p>Arabic theological treatise on the catechism of divine unity attributed in the subscription to ʿAllāmah al-Davvānī, who may be the same as Jalāl al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Asʿad al-Davvānī (d. 907/1501). 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Neat, miniscule naskh. 
</p>
                        <p>Verses (ghazal) ascribed to the poet Ṣāʾib appended at end (f. 4v) by a later hand. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21683">al-Taḥqīq fī kalimat al-tawḥīd</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21683">التّحقيق فى كلمة التّوحيد</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1162-item2">
                     <locus from="5v" to="12v">ff. 5v-12v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656324.0x000001 viaf_11716360">Yaʿqūb ibn ʿUs̲mān ibn Maḥmūd Ghaznavī Charkhī (d. 838/1434-5)</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656324.0x000001 viaf_11716360">يعقوب چرخى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21751">Risālah-'i ṣifat-i Awliyāʾ Allāh</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21751">رسالهٴ صفت اولياء الله</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Treatise on the supernatural powers of Ṣūfī saints concluding with the view that there is always a quṭb or leading (‘pole’) saint in the world at any one time by Yaʿqūb ibn ʿUs̲mān ibn Maḥmūd al-Ghaznavī al-Charkhī (d. 838/1434-5).
</p>
                        <p>Some folios are disordered and lost. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Neat Persian naskh throughout, with some alternation to early nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                        <p>Verses (ghazal and rubāʿī) ascribed to the poets Aṣafī and Ṣāʾib appended at beginning (f. 5r) by a later hand. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1162-item3">
                     <locus from="12v" to="16r">ff. 12v-16r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Untitled commentary on a rubāʿī by the Ṣūfī saint, Abū Saʿīd ibn Abū al-Khayr by the theologian and author of a tafsīr of the Qurʾān, Yaʿqūb ibn ʿUs̲mān ibn Maḥmūd Ghaznavī Charkhī (d. 838/1434-5), a disciple of Bahāʾ al-Dīn Muḥammad Bukhārī the Naqshband (d. 791/1388).
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 16r): completed by Ḥasan ibn Ḥusayn Ḥiṣārī, known as Bābā Shaykh Halghatavī (?), of the village of Kish (south of Samarqand), Shavvāl 992/October 1584. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656324.0x000001 viaf_11716360" type="supplied">Yaʿqūb ibn ʿUs̲mān ibn Maḥmūd Ghaznavī Charkhī (d. 838/1434-5)</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656324.0x000001 viaf_11716360" type="supplied">يعقوب چرخى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1162-item4">
                     <locus from="17v" to="39r">ff. 17v-39r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item d. </p>
                        <p>Rare untitled autobiography of Bahāʾ al-Dīn Muḥammad Bukhārī the Naqshband (d. 791/1388) dictated to his disciple, the theologian and author of a tafsīr of the Qurʾān, Yaʿqūb ibn ʿUs̲mān ibn Maḥmūd Ghaznavī Charkhī (d. 838/1434-5), containing the saint’s spiritual genealogy to ʿAbd al-Khāliq Ghujdavānī. 
</p>
                        <p>The work was apparently written at the tomb of Sayf al-Dīn Bākharzī in Fatḥābād. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 39r): completed 992/1584-5. 
</p>
                        <p>Neat s̲uls̲, naskh, and nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                        <p>Verses (ghazal and mas̲navī) ascribed to the poet Ṣāʾib appended at end (f. 39v) by a later hand. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName key="viaf_11716360" type="supplied" xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Charkhī, Yaʿqūb, -1447</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="viaf_11716360">يعقوب چرخى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
